reviews.review_text: R I P Jerry Moore R I P Jerry Moore , a true pioneer of the first GD tapers ...

The Highs are High and the Lows are Low First of all, this is a wonderful sounding AUD.  The high points here, Peggy-O (a very very good version) and The Other One through Dark Star, are beautiful.  The lows, starting with Promised Land and a messy Minglewood, to name a few, are distracted and disjointed.  Overall, not exceptional, not terrible.
